    lesson: 'The to-complete performance index (TCPI) is the cost efficiency the remaining work must achieve to hit a target (TCPI = (BAC - EV) / (BAC - AC) against the original budget). A TCPI above 1 means the team must outperform the original plan to recover — generally a red flag that the target is unrealistic. Below 1 means there is slack. It converts "are we recoverable?" into a single ratio.',
